{"id":1907,"date":"2012-03-30T06:31:46","date_gmt":"2012-03-30T11:31:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_for_the_people.php"},"modified":"2012-03-30T06:31:46","modified_gmt":"2012-03-30T11:31:46","slug":"beer_for_the_people","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_for_the_people.php","title":{"rendered":"Beer for the People"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_logo.gif\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>First brewed in 1893 and originally named Cerveza Cuauht&eacute;moc after the sixteenth-century Mexican emperor, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.indio.com.mx\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Indio<\/a>, as it quickly became called by consumers and renamed as such in 1905, is a dark (and super tasty) beer produced by Cervecer&iacute;a Cuauht&eacute;moc Moctezuma, part of global brewery Heineken. This week Indio introduced a new logo and packaging designed by <strike>Mexico City-based <a href=\"http:\/\/www.och.com.mx\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Olabuenaga Chemistri<\/a><\/strike> London-based <a href=\"http:\/\/www.wearebulletproof.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bulletproof<\/a>.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>Finally, Ricardo Duran, CM Brand Manager, explained the changes and said that inspired by the traditional Aztec calendar, &#8220;create a new element that allows us to complement the iconic image of the emperor Cuauhtemoc. This innovative design gives Indio a much stronger, commanding presence and a warrior attitude worthy of our beer.&#8221; We are convinced that this is a very positive change and provides significant benefits to the mark, since it offers robust tools to continue building the Indio leadership position deserves, he said.<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/economia.terra.com.mx\/noticias\/noticia.aspx?idNoticia=201203282145_AGE_81036926\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Press Release<\/a> (Google translated)<\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_bottle.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_old.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">A closer look at the old label. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.flickr.com\/photos\/rsinghabout\/2500923661\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Photo by Flickr user rsinghabout<\/a><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_botella.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p>As a counterpoint to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/less_calories_more_crop.php\">this week&#8217;s Miller64<\/a>, Indio has plenty of street cred and oomph. Its old look wasn&#8217;t anything particularly good or even different from other lower-priced Mexican beers with a basic logo and realistic illustration. The new packaging shows Mr. Cuauht&eacute;moc on steroids, ready to kick ass and then down a &#8220;cahuama&#8221; (a &#8220;Forty&#8221; if you will). Kidding aside, the gold and dark green palette looks stunning on this beer, even if it&#8217;s a common combination &mdash; most notably used by another Mexican beer, Dos Equis. The touch of red on the emperor&#8217;s headpiece is a nice flair. The packaging starts to lose some of its power in the 6- and 12-packs where it looks more commercial and like American beer packaging. No offense. All in all, a vast improvement where visuals match content.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_cahuama.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_lata.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_carton.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_sixpack.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_photo_01.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" width=\"574\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/cerveza_indio_photo_02.jpg\" alt=\"Cerveza Indio\" width=\"574\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Update found via <a href=\"http:\/\/nfgraphics.com\/nueva-imagen-de-cerveza-indio\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Nice Fucking Graphics<\/a>.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_120330_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_120330_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"574\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gif\" alt=\"Voting Begins\" \/>\n<table class=\"table\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\t<tr valign=\"top\">\n        <!--VOTE CONCEPT-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t\t<div id = \"pollDiv1\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/td>\n\t<\/tr>\n<\/table>\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_end.gif\" alt=\"Voting Ends\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format"